<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 24px;
        color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
      }
      table {
        max-width: 600px;
        padding: 0 12px 24px 12px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
      }
      tr {
        text-align: left;
      }
      hr {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      a {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:link {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:visited {
        color: #4c6259;
      }
      a:hover {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:active {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      .article-title {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .text-centered {
        text-align: center;
      }
      .pb-s {
        padding-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .pb-m {
        padding-bottom: 24px;
      }
      .pb-l {
        padding-bottom: 48px;
      }
      .pb-xl {
        padding-bottom: 56px;
      }
      .color-main {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .font-s {
        font-size: 12px;
      }
    </style>
    <title>AR Weekly</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <table class="text-centered">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-centered">
            <img
              src="<%= @logo_url %>"
              alt="AR Weekly"
              width="100px"
              height="100px"
            />
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-centered font-s pb-xl">
            Issue #<%= @issue_number %>, <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date, "{D} {Mfull} {YYYY}") %>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-xl">
            Hello guys! This digest covers Augmented Reality related news between <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date_from, "{D} {Mfull}") %> and <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date_to, "{D} {Mfull}") %>. Enjoy!
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Harry Potter: Wizards Unite - Gameplay Footage and Pre-Registration
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            It's most likely going to be the next big hit in AR gaming. After Ingress and Pok√©mon GO, Harry Potter: Wizards Unite, is the third game from developer Niantic. From this week on, Android users are able to pre-register via the Play Store. If you are interested in gameplay footage and in-depth game description, you will enjoy the following article ;-)
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://mobile-ar.reality.news/news/niantic-conjures-preview-harry-potter-augmented-reality-game-opens-pre-registration-google-play-0194677")) %>'
              >https://mobile-ar.reality.news</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Apple World Wide Developer Conference (WWDC) from June 3 to June 7
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            This years WWDC will take place from June 3 to June 7. The most interesting part from an AR's point of view will be the keynote on the first day. Expected announcements are iOS 13, macOS 10.15, watchOS 6, and tvOS 13. Maybe we get lucky and get some infos on the iPhone tethered AR glasses we mentioned last week.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://developer.apple.com/wwdc19")) %>'
              >https://developer.apple.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Google Maps as a Game Platform
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            A year ago Google released a Google Maps API to build games based on real-world locations. Real-world buildings, roads, and parks can be turned into game objects. Combined with a real-time global understanding of the world this provides a powerful platform to build immersive mobile games. In the latest update Google Maps is adding new kind of terrain details, support for path finding, and access to biome data to access information about a location's land cover type.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://venturebeat.com/2019/03/15/google-maps-platform-adds-new-styles-and-gameplay-options-for-mobile-games")) %>'
              >https://venturebeat.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              AR SketchWalk: Experience 2D Sketch In the Real World
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            Morpholio Trace is a Sketch CAD App for iPhones. The latest version introduces AR SketchWalk, which lets you experience the 2D designs in the real world. Thanks to ARKit 2 support for shared sessions, the experience is even multiuser capable.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://venturebeat.com/2019/03/12/morpholio-lets-you-jump-into-a-sketch-in-augmented-reality")) %>'
              >https://venturebeat.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            Suggestions or comments are more than welcome! Just reply to this
            email.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-xl">
            Thanks for reading<br />
            <span class="color-main"><strong>AR</strong>&nbsp;Weekly</span>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m font-s">
            You receive this Email because you are subscribed to the AR Weekly
            Blog. Your next delivery is on <%= Timex.format!(@next_issue_date, "{D} {Mfull} {YYYY}") %>.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-s">
            <a href="<%= @unsubscribe_url %>">Unsubscribe</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
            |&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="<%= @privacy_url %>">Privacy Policy</a
            >&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="mailto:hello@ar-weekly.blog">hello@ar-weekly.blog</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/Domeee/ar-weekly">Source Code @ GitHub</a>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <img width="1px" height="1px" src="<%= @issue_tracking_url %>" alt="">
  </body>
</html>
